Article 18 The fire control bureau of the Ministry of Public Security is the registration and examination and approval department for the qualification of first-class registered fire control engineer. The fire control institutions of the public security organs of provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government are the registration and examination and approval departments for the qualification of second-class registered fire control engineer.Article 19 A person who has obtained the qualification certificate of Class I or Class II registered fire control engineer and applies for registration shall be employed by an approved fire control technical service institution or key unit of fire control safety, and shall apply to the place where the unit is located through the employing unit.Article 20 After receiving the registration application materials from the applicant, if the application materials are incomplete or do not conform to the legal form, the fire control institution of the public security organ of the province, autonomous region or municipality directly under the Central Government shall, on the spot or within 5 working days, inform the applicant once of all the contents that need to be supplemented and corrected.Article 21 The fire control institutions of the public security organs of provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government shall, within 20 working days from the date of accepting the registration application,Complete the preliminary examination of the application materials for the registration of the qualification of Class I registered fire engineer and the registration examination and approval of the qualification of Class II registered fire engineer in accordance with the prescribed conditions and procedures, and submit the application materials for the registration of the qualification of Class I registered fire engineer and the preliminary examination opinions to the fire control bureau of the Ministry of Public Security for examination and approval. The fire control bureau of the Ministry of Public Security shall, from the date of receiving the application materials and preliminary examination opinions submitted by the fire control institution of the provincial public security organ,The applicant shall make a decision on whether to approve the application within 20 working days. If the decision on approval cannot be made within the prescribed time limit, the applicant shall be informed of the time limit for extension and the reasons therefor. Article 22 The registration examination and approval department shall, within 10 working days from the date of making the approval decision, issue and serve the registration certificate of the corresponding level. Article 23 Each registration of the registration certificate shall be valid for 3 years. The registration certificate shall be the practice certificate of the registered fire control engineer of the corresponding level within the validity period.Article 24 Those who apply for initial registration shall apply within one year from the date of obtaining the qualification certificate of Class I and Class II registered fire control engineers.Article 25 Continuing education is a necessary condition for the renewal of registration, re-registration and overdue initial registration of a registered fire engineer. Within the validity period of each registration, registered fire engineers at all levels shall complete corresponding continuing education in accordance with the provisions. Article 26 The registration examination and approval department shall timely announce to the public the relevant information on the registration of registered fire engineers, establish the integrity files of registered fire engineers, and implement credit management on their practice activities. Article 27 The registration management departments of the registered fire engineer qualification at all levels shall strictly implement the relevant provisions of the Administrative Licensing Law of the People's Republic of China. Today's examination information sharing ends here, hoping to give you some help. Everyone must work hard to prepare for the exam and strive to pass the fire engineer exam as soon as possible!
